definitions.definition: Miscellaneous items of little value , especially discarded or unwanted items.
examples: This shed is full of junk – will you help me sort it out?
She needs to find a better place to keep her junk [= belongings].

definitions.definition: ( attributive ) Material or resources of poor quality or low value , especially resources that lack commercial value.

examples: The student put down junk for answers just to finish his homework more quickly.

definitions.definition: ( slang ) Any narcotic drug , especially heroin .
( slang ) The genitalia , especially of a male .
Pieces of old cable or cordage , used for making gaskets , mats , swabs , etc., and when picked to pieces, forming oakum for filling the seams of ships .
( dated , countable ) A fragment of any solid substance ; a thick piece; a chunk .
